        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A pointer to the internal buffer of unread data for "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "stream"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", if possible; "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NULL"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " otherwise. The buffer is good only until the next stream operation called on the stream. You should neither change the contents of the returned buffer nor attempt to deallocate the buffer; it is still owned by the stream. The bytes returned in the buffer are considered read from the stream."
